According to the {{ill|Nihon Shoki|lt=Chronicles of Japan|ja|日本書紀|12=draft|12=draft}}<ref group="原">『日本書紀』崇神天皇48th year 正月戊子（10日）条。</ref>, in the 48th year of Emperor Sujin's reign, the Emperor instructed Toyoki no Mikoto and Ikume no Mikoto (later Emperor Suinin) to each have a dream to determine the successor. Toyoki no Mikoto dreamed of climbing Mount Mimoro (Mount Miwa) and waving spears and swords to the east. Ikume no Mikoto dreamed of climbing the same mountain, spreading ropes in all directions, and chasing away sparrows. Based on these dreams, it was decided that Ikume no Mikoto, who envisioned securing territories and promoting agriculture, would inherit the throne, while Toyoki no Mikoto, who wielded weapons toward the east, would be sent to govern the eastern regions.
== Burial ==
The burial site of Toyoki no Mikoto is unknown. The {{ill|Futagoyama Kofun|ja|総社二子山古墳|1=Sōja Futagoyama Kofun|12=draft|12=draft}} in {{ill|Maebashi|ja|前橋市|12=draft|12=draft}}, Gunma Prefecture, was traditionally regarded as his tomb until investigations dated the tomb to the late 6th century. Other theories suggest the {{ill|Ōmuro Kofun Cluster|ja|大室古墳群|12=draft|12=draft}} in Maebashi or the {{ill|Maruyama Kofun (Ishioka)|ja|丸山古墳 (石岡市)|12=draft|12=draft}} in Ishioka, Ibaraki Prefecture.
